    "content_hash": "7b103a73f2d3b672",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About ALSO.\n\nWe’re ALSO, an electric mobility company originally conceived as a part of Rivian. We’re a passionate team of builders, dreamers, doers and innovators, focused on creating entirely new (not to mention, innovative and delightful) vertically integrated, small EVs designed to meet the global mobility challenges of today and tomorrow. Our mission is to inspire everyone to ride ALSO—replacing many local car, truck and SUV miles with ones on vehicles that are more affordable, more enjoyable and 10-50x more efficient.\n\nALSO is looking for a Sr Staff Battery Pack Design Engineer to bridge the critical gap between mature product design and mass production. You will not just be designing; you will be the driving force that takes our battery packs from the lab to the assembly line. In this role, you will own the technical execution of battery modules and packs as they transition through validation and into launch.\n\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n - Mechanical Design Improvements: Lead the Battery pack design improvements by building prototypes, DOE test plans inhouse and at CMs. Drive design for manufacturing improvements at component suppliers and FATP CMs.\n\n - Validation \u0026 Compliance: Ensure designs meet strict mechanical (shock/vibe), environmental (thermal/humidity), and safety (propagation/crush) requirements. You will interpret test failures and drive design tweaks to ensure passing results.\n\n - Global CM Management \u0026 Technical Liaison: Act as the primary technical liaison with engineering headquarters and Battery Contract Manufacturers. Rigorously review First Article Inspections (FAI) and analyze CPK/PPK data to ensure the manufacturing process is stable and components meet specifications. Lead onsite execution (2-6 weeks/year travel) to resolve production bottlenecks .\n\n - Quality and reliability focus: Define and scope lifecycle test needs associated with improving quality, and reliability components, assembly quality and reliability.\n\nWhat You Will Bring\n\n - Education: Must have a Mechanical Engineering degree with a strong engineering and physics fundamentals\n\n - Experience: 8 - 10+ years in battery engineering with experience in cell selection, module hardware, and electrical interconnects. Proven ability to lead and execute distinct projects focused on advancing battery platform technologies.\n\n - Testing Standards: Deep understanding of design requirements for meeting battery safety and reliability standards (e.g., UN 38.3, UL 1642, SAE J2464).\n\n - Technical Mindset: Strong grasp of first principles thinking; you solve novel problems by looking at the physics, not just industry trends.\n\n - Fast-Paced: Comfortable working in a high-velocity environment where priorities can shift rapidly.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n - Expertise in 3D modeling and drafting in Catia V6. Structural and thermal simulation experience with Anys, Altair or similar CAE software.\n\n - Familiarity with laser welding, wire bonding, and ultrasonic welding processes.\n\n - Experience designing for high-volume automated assembly lines.\n\n - Knowledge of battery safety standards (e.g., UN 38.3, UL 1642/1973).\n\nThe salary for this position ranges from $220,000 to $260,000 per year, depending on experience and qualifications.\n\nWhy ALSO.\n\nWe’re passionate about helping the world find a better way to get there—wherever it is you’re headed.\n\nWe’re located in the heart of Silicon Valley and have brought together a world-class team from some of the biggest brands in the technology, automotive, cycling, outdoor recreation and retail spaces. \n\nTogether we’re working hands-on to imagine, design and build an entirely new solution to a global set of transportation challenges. \n\nPerks and Benefits\n\n - Robust health coverage. Excellent health, dental and vision insurance covered up to 100% by ALSO with FSA \u0026 HSA options.\n\n - One Medical membership and dedicated insurance advocates.\n\n - Rich fertility and family building benefits with Progyny.\n\n - Flexible time off. \n\n - 401(k) match.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
